table abc_extra191.abc_ABCMeta_mro_identity:
  description: "abc.ABCMeta MRO identity checks in abcmro191 namespace — ABCMeta.__mro__.__len__()==3 (ABCMeta MRO is [ABCMeta, type, object]; as a metaclass ABCMeta inherits from type, which in turn inherits from object, giving a 3-entry MRO); ABCMeta.__mro__[0].__name__=='ABCMeta' (len=7: 'ABC'=3+'Meta'=4=7; first MRO entry is always the class itself); ABCMeta.__mro__[1].__name__=='type' (len=4; ABCMeta's direct base is the built-in metaclass type); ABCMeta.__mro__.__len__ (3) > ABC.__mro__.__len__ (2) by 1 — metaclass chain is one step longer; ABCMeta.__mro__[1].__name__ (4: 'type') < ABC.__mro__[1].__name__ (6: 'object') — type is shorter than object; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: ABCMeta_mro
  id_prefix: abcmro191

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - ["abcmeta_mro_len",    "abc.ABCMeta.__mro__.__len__",                  [],          3,    "abc.ABCMeta.__mro__.__len__() == 3 (MRO is [ABCMeta, type, object]); verified Python 3.14.3"]
